    fact: "Jebel Hafeet is a limestone mountain about 1,240 metres high on the UAE–Oman border, rising above the oasis city of Al Ain. It is the highest peak in the Emirate of Abu Dhabi. Its folded rock holds marine fossils from an ancient seabed, and the Bronze Age beehive tombs at its foot gave their name to the Hafit period (about 3200–2600 BC).",
