    subject: "Mount Kenya", icon: "", category: "mountain", tags: ["unesco"],
    easy: "In East Africa, in Kenya, an extinct volcano lifts jagged, snow-dusted peaks high above the clouds — the second-highest mountain on the whole continent. Photograph the mountain.",
    medium: "Word from the highlands near the equator in Africa: an ancient, worn-down volcano raises rocky spires so high that small glaciers cling on even under the tropical sun, and a nearby people once believed their god lived on its icy crown. Photograph the peak.",
    hard: "An old volcano, long gone quiet, wears a crown of rocky spires so lofty that little glaciers survive even though the burning sun of the middle of the world beats down; herders in its foothills long held it sacred as the home of their god. Bring me the icy summit.",
    fact: "Mount Kenya is an extinct volcano and, at 5,199 metres, the second-highest mountain in Africa. It still carries about 11 small glaciers, which are shrinking fast, and its national park is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.",
