    easy: "In East Africa, in Rwanda, one of the continent's oldest mountain rainforests rings with the calls of black-and-white monkeys that gather in troops hundreds strong. Photograph the colobus monkeys.",
    medium: "Word from a misty mountain rainforest in the heart of Africa: black-and-white, long-tailed monkeys with capes of white fur crowd together in huge family bands high in the ancient trees, near where a first trickle of a great northern river is born. Photograph the leaping monkeys.",
    hard: "Deep in one of the oldest cloud-forests anywhere, sleek black monkeys draped in white capes and long tails huddle in bands of many dozens among dripping branches — and from these hills seeps one of the farthest beginnings of a mighty river that flows to a distant sea. Bring me the caped tree-dwellers.",
    fact: "Nyungwe National Park in Rwanda is one of Africa's oldest and largest mountain rainforests and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. It shelters 13 kinds of primates, including black-and-white Ruwenzori colobus monkeys, which live in some of the biggest troops known for any colobus — sometimes several hundred together.",
