    fact: "The Djinguereber Mosque in Timbuktu, Mali, was built of mud brick around 1327 during the reign of the wealthy emperor Mansa Musa, and it became one of West Africa's great centres of Islamic learning; it is a UNESCO World Heritage Site.",
