    subject: "The Roman ruins of Dougga", icon: "", category: "ruins", tags: ["ancient","unesco","roman"],
    easy: "In North Africa, in Tunisia, a hilltop in green countryside holds the best-preserved small Roman town in the region, crowned by a temple with tall Corinthian columns. Photograph the ancient ruins.",
    medium: "Word from a green North African hillside: scattered across the fields stand the temples, theatre, and paved streets of a little town abandoned long ago — its grandest temple still raising a row of tall columns to the sky. Photograph the hilltop ruins.",
    hard: "Once a Numidian royal seat, then a prosperous Roman country town, this hilltop settlement was left in open fields and so escaped later cities' sprawl. Its capitol temple, theatre, and a strange pointed mausoleum still stand among the grass. Bring me the well-preserved ancient town.",
    fact: "Dougga (Roman Thugga) in northern Tunisia is often called the best-preserved Roman small town in North Africa; set in open countryside, its 2nd-century Capitol temple and theatre still stand among the ruins. It became a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1997.",
